This paper discusses decentralized trust management and its application in open collaborative systems. It analyzes the risk factors and adverse effects of different threat models, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses trust aggregation models and metrics, which can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the study involves analyzing and comparing different trust aggregation methods, which can be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
